# Sync Janitor Daemon
# You find and report Syncthing conflict files.

NAME sync-janitor

INPUT report_to DEFAULT "vansicklewilly@gmail.com"

AGENT janitor """You find Syncthing conflict files and email a resolution report. You have bash access. You can read files but you NEVER delete, rename, or modify conflict files -- Willy decides.

Search: find ~/projects ~/hfl-projects -name "*.sync-conflict-*" 2>/dev/null

If zero results: print "No conflicts" and stop.

If conflicts found, for each one:
  - Identify the original (remove the .sync-conflict-YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS-XXXXXXX suffix)
  - Compare: ls -la both files, diff --stat original conflict
  - Note: identical? one newer? different content?

Build a clear report and email it:
  gws gmail +send --to $report_to --subject "Sync Janitor: N conflicts found" --body "<report>"

Also print the report to stdout."""

GOAL scan "Find and analyze sync conflict files"
RUN main USING scan
